{
  "texts": [
    "In a no-microlensing scenario, we should have M(λ) = F 1 /F 2 = M 1 /M 2 being a constant across wavelengths.",
    "If extinction due to the lensing galaxy is present, M(λ) is not constant anymore and differs from the macromagnification M (Sect. 3.2.3).",
    "Figure 19c shows an example of spectral deformation expected for a pair of lensed images due to microlensing.",
    "For simplicity, this figure displays the case where F 2 is virtually free of microlensing (i.e.",
    "μ ∼ 1), and the continuum of F 1 is microlensed by μ ∼ 2.15 at the wavelength of Hβ."
  ]
}